article.headline: Penn St. 72, Mount St. Mary's 43
article.story: STATE COLLEGE, Pa. -- Tim Frazier led five Penn State players in double figures with 15 points Sunday and the Nittany Lions defeated Mount St. Mary's 72-43 on Sunday, snapping a three-game losing streak. Cammeron Woodyard had 14 points, Billy Oliver 13 and Jermaine Marshall and Sasa Borovnjak scored 10 points apiece as Penn State (7-5) ended the game on a 27-9 run. The Mountaineers (1-9) got 11 points from Raven Barber and 10 from Chad Holley. Penn State connected on nine of its first 11 field goal attempts of the second half and led 50-34 after Frazier scored on a drive with just over 11 minutes remaining. Frazier extended the lead to 20 at 54-34 with a coast-to-coast layup two minutes later. The Nittany Lions shot 67 percent from the field in the second half. Penn State shot 36 percent from the field in the first half and led 28-25 at the break.
